parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Filler Neck Corrosion and Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and leaks in the fuel filler neck can cause fuel spills, odors, and potentially lead to fires or explosions, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline when filling the tank
visible fuel leaks or pools of gasoline under the vehicle
rust or corrosion on the fuel filler neck or surrounding components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lock-up of the rear seatbelts can cause discomfort and potentially lead to unsafe situations where passengers may need to remove their seatbelts while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The rear seatbelts lock up or become overly tight
causing discomfort and restricting movement
passengers need to remove their seatbelts to readjust
the belts get tighter and tighter if not taken off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sharp Plastic Component in Rear Seat Area
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sharp plastic component in the rear seat area can cause cuts and lacerations to passengers, potentially leading to injuries.
symptoms: Passengers may experience cuts or lacerations from coming into contact with the sharp plastic disk
the component is as sharp as a knife
the injury can occur during normal entry or exit from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive glare from the headlights can cause temporary blindness or distraction to oncoming traffic, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to fatalities.
symptoms: Blinding or excessive glare from the headlights
difficulty seeing the road ahead
discomfort or pain from the intense light
feeling of being "dazzled" or disoriented.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly gain speed, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
continues to gain speed even when the foot is removed from the accelerator pedal
and may require riding the brakes to slow down or maintain a safe speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical shortage in the driver seat heater can cause the seat to become extremely hot, potentially scorching the seat and posing a burn risk to the driver.
symptoms: The driver seat becomes extremely hot while driving
the seat is scorching or burning
there is an unusual smell of burning or melting plastic.
